description: From Middle English unserchable, equivalent to un- +‎ searchable.

adjectives.description: unsearchable (comparative more unsearchable, superlative most unsearchable)

entries.meaning: That cannot be investigated or searched into; unknowable, inscrutable.
examples: Preachers warned […] that although God might sometimes make the meaning of his judgements clear they were normally unsearchable.

entries.meaning: That cannot be sought out or looked for.
(computing, Internet) Not capable of being searched; on which one cannot perform a search.
